HEADWORD: Tipping
<hw>Tip"ping</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A
distinct articulation given in playing quick notes on the flute, by
striking the tongue against the roof of the mouth;
double-tonguing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tipple</ent>⟦br⟧
